>  Just because your Java program compiles does not mean it has no errors <i>(even type errors)</i>.<p>This is because<p>a) Java allows arbitrary subtype casting of object reference types<p><pre><code>    Object s = "string"; 
    Integer foo(Integer i) {
       return i.intValue() + 2;
    }
    foo((Integer) s); //runtime error
</code></pre>
b) null is valid value for all object reference variables.<p><pre><code>    foo(null); //runtime error

</code></pre>
Java should not be used to point out the faults of static typing.

